    <h2>What are Cookies?</h2>
    <p>Cookies are small text files stored on your device when you visit a website. They are used to improve the browsing experience and to collect statistical information.</p>

    <h2>Types of Cookies We Use</h2>

    <h3>Technical Cookies (Necessary)</h3>
    <p>They are essential for the website to function. They enable navigation and use of basic features. They do not require consent.</p>

    <h3>Analytical Cookies</h3>
    <p>They allow us to analyze user behavior in aggregate to improve the website. We use Google Analytics 4 with IP anonymization.</p>

    <h3>Preference Cookies</h3>
    <p>They store user preferences (language, region) to personalize the experience.</p>

    <h2>Cookie Management</h2>
    <p>You can configure your browser to reject cookies or to alert you when a website tries to place a cookie. Please note that rejecting technical cookies may affect how the site functions.</p>

    <h2>Updates to this Policy</h2>
    <p>This cookie policy may be updated periodically. We recommend reviewing it regularly.</p>
